
'''= to promote and discover the use of open source software and open stardards in archaeological research'''

URL = http://www.iosa.it/


=Description=

"IOSA is a project carried on by grupporicerche, to promote and discover the use of open source software and open standards in archaeological research. There's a growing focus on data sharing as a major issue that involves research, computing and legal concerns.

Our latest creation is Quantitative Archaeology Wiki, where you can find documentation and tutorials for using free software in quantitative and spatial archaeological analyses. The wiki is open for all those who have written or want to write free documentation, released under the GNU FDL.

The IOSA project has been presented at recent scientific meetings. It is part of an unformal network of people (rather than organizations) distributed all across Europe, summing up the efforts of archeologists and other people from the IT and Computer Science fields.

Users are encouraged to join the international mailing list and give their contribution to the on-going discussion. The mailing list archives are also available on Gmane. IOSA.it is here as a service for anyone interested in open and free archaeology."
(http://www.iosa.it/)


